"    Predictive value of serum markers for coronary heart disease",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 468px; height: 528px; background-image: url(data:image/gif;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    This figure shows hazard ratios for future cardiac events in initially healthy women comparing extreme quintiles for individual prognostic variables (red) and for lipid ratios (blue) and adjusted for age, blood pressure, body mass index, diabetes, and current smoking status. The hazard ratios compare those in the highest quintile of the prognostic variable with those in the lowest quintile or, for the hazard ratios marked with an asterisk (*), the lowest quintile with the highest quintile. Black bars represent 95% confidence intervals.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"     Apo: apolipoprotein; CRP: C-reactive protein; LDL: low density lipoprotein; HDL: high density lipoprotein.",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"     Data from: Ridker, PM, Rifai, N, Cook, NR, et al. JAMA 2005; 294:326.",
"    </div>",
"   </div>",
